Citations
Date: 20/1/1933
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 13
Edition:
Quote: Shedding is common among hairy sickle-fibres; sometimes all are shed, while occasionally, at the other extreme, all persist, every intermediate condition being found. Many of these fibres are much shorter than any shed hairy sickle-fibres.
